research_municipality_step.notes: Woodbridge Township operates under the Mayor-Council system of government, as per the Faulkner Act (Mayor-Council Plan F). The Mayor and four at-large council members are elected to four-year terms, with their elections typically coinciding. The five ward council members are also elected to four-year terms, with their elections staggered two years after the mayoral and at-large elections. Mayor John E. McCormac was re-elected in November 2023, with his term expected to end in December 2027. The at-large council members Kyle M. Anderson, Lizbeth DeJesus, Gregg M. Ficarra, and Brian F. Small were elected in 2023, with terms ending in 2027. The ward council members Cory S. Spillar (Third Ward), Harold R. Bauer Jr. (Second Ward), Sharon McAuliffe (First Ward), Debbie Meehan (Fifth Ward), and Virbhadra N. Patel (Fourth Ward) were re-elected in the November 2025 general election, with their terms now extending to 2029. The official Woodbridge Township website lists these nine council members. A news report from November 2025 mentioned 'Current Councilman Daniel Harris' winning an at-large seat, but this name is not consistently present across the official township website or the comprehensive Wikipedia list of current council members. Therefore, Daniel Harris has not been included in this list based on the primary sources.
